        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1235143815" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15312173625765854337">Dark Horizons picks up right where the first book finished with Lexi recovering from her faceoff with Nathan. In this book we&apos;ll see the three teens finishing up their difficult high school senior year. There is no end to the issues in this thrill ride. As another reviewer said it is aptly titled because the three are looking forward, but the horizon isn&apos;t much brighter from where they stand now than before.<br/><br/>That said, the twists and turns Hermann put in this book keep you turning pages. The bull</span>
  <span id="freeText15312173625765854337" style="display:none">Dark Horizons picks up right where the first book finished with Lexi recovering from her faceoff with Nathan. In this book we'll see the three teens finishing up their difficult high school senior year. There is no end to the issues in this thrill ride. As another reviewer said it is aptly titled because the three are looking forward, but the horizon isn't much brighter from where they stand now than before.<br /><br />That said, the twists and turns Hermann put in this book keep you turning pages. The bully issue is still prevalent, but there are other issues the young people have to deal with. Sometimes they deal with them together and other times as individuals. It gives a realistic look at how lonely teens can feel when they are on the cusp of adulthood. The question of the day is will they move into adulthood stronger for what they've faced, or will the horizon be forever dark?</span>
  <a data-text-id="15312173625765854337" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
